      "id": "893956507135077",
      "score": 4,
      "review_title": "It's much better now!",
      "review_description": "I was very surprised when I entered this game after so many months... The new update really impressed me! New monsters, no more evil moderators, and so on. Now this game deserves 4 stars from me, it will be 5 stars if you fix the bugs and add a lot of new stuff. Here's an example of what to add in the next update: First: fix the mirror in the lobby, when I look at it, everything lags and slows down, my friends have the same problem. Just add normal optimization to the mirror. Second: add normal screenshots from the game to this site, since you have screenshots from the old Lethal Ape 3 and the game doesn't match your screenshots, because the screenshots are not from this game. Third: add normal physics to the pool on the second floor and add a normal model for the railings and stairs in the same location where the pool is, as well as on the first floor where there is a machine device, and add a normal model for it, as everyone can pass through this device because it does not have a normal model. Fourth: don't add more monsters in the next update (there are already too many of them). Fifth: create a separate room in the lobby with all the monsters and their names. Sixth: fix the bug where there is some kind of command bar in the upper left corner of the game screen, remove it. Seventh: add physics to the player's death, so that when he dies, there will be drops of blood and a body (like in the previous part of the game, Lethal Ape) Eighth: Add more distant and high-quality rendering to the game. Ninth: make the elevator work with players, i.e. when I call the elevator and my friends are there, I press the button and only I can ride without them, fix this! Tenth: In the next update, make that when the game starts, the message “Welcome to Lethal Ape 3”. I hope you will add this in the next update/updates. Thank you very much for already fixing several bugs in this game, including moderators and many monsters. Good luck with the game development, dear developers!",
      "date": 1764175689,
